The integument coloration at posterior third of elytra varies from dark to light brown (especially in specimens from 
Venezuela
). Also, the greyish pubescence may be denser in some specimens (
Fig. 10
)
. The posterior third of elytra varies from slightly yellowish green to light or darker brown. In some specimens (especially those from 
Peru
and 
Bolivia
) the elytral apex may be more angular but not with
